Male Tergum X membranous, with one pair of relatively long, robust dorsal processes, relatively widely separated, slightly tapered distally (
Fig. 170
). Superior appendages slightly dorso-ventrally flattened in distal half; in lateral view, relatively slender, length about 5 times width, tapered in distal half (
Fig. 168
); in dorsal view, length about 4.5 times width, with one pair of long mesal spines and several pairs of shorter spines distally (
Fig. 170
). Phallus simple, tube-like (
Fig. 168
). Inferior appendages short; in ventral view, fused in basal half, dilated and truncated distally, with oval excision meso-distally, length about 0.4 times width (
Fig. 169
); in lateral view, slender, length about 4 times width (
Fig. 168
).

Female. Genitalia with a single slender, elongate mesal process on sternite VIII; segment IX relatively long, tapered slightly distally, segment X relatively short and segments IX and X relatively slender (
Fig. 195
).
